## 🚨 Containment Steps – Data Exfiltration Response

> **⚡ CRITICAL: Execute all phases in order. Every checkbox must be ticked. Data exfiltration is a NOTIFIABLE BREACH under GDPR/HIPAA/PCI-DSS — escalate to {{ dpo_contact | default("the Data Protection Officer") }} and legal (`{{ legal_contact | default("legal@phantomnet.local") }}`) immediately.**

---

### 🔴 Phase 1 · Immediate Isolation & Traffic Block `(T+0 → T+15 min)`

> Goal: Stop active exfiltration NOW while preserving forensic evidence.

- [ ] **🚨 DO NOT reboot or power off `{{ source_ip | default("<source_host>") }}`** – A live system preserves memory forensics (encryption keys, process tree, open file handles). Shutdown destroys this evidence.

- [ ] **Capture live memory from `{{ source_ip | default("<source_host>") }}`** – Before any network isolation, dump RAM:
  ```bash
  # Linux – using LiME kernel module
  sudo insmod lime.ko "path=/tmp/mem_dump_{{ source_ip | default("host") }}_$(date +%s).lime format=lime"

  # Windows – using WinPmem
  winpmem.exe -o C:\forensics\mem_{{ source_ip | default("host") }}_$(Get-Date -Format yyyyMMddHHmmss).raw

  # Verify dump integrity
  sha256sum /tmp/mem_dump_*.lime > /tmp/mem_dump.sha256
  ```

- [ ] **Isolate source host `{{ source_ip | default("<source_host>") }}`** – Cut network access without shutdown:
  ```bash
  # Linux – drop all outbound traffic (preserve inbound for forensic access)
  iptables -I OUTPUT -s {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }} -j DROP
  # Block at SDN / switch level for total isolation
  phantomnet-sdn isolate --host {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }} --preserve-mgmt
  # Windows host – isolate via NetSh
  netsh advfirewall set allprofiles firewallpolicy blockinbound,blockoutbound
  ```

- [ ] **Block destination at perimeter firewall** – Immediately block all traffic to `{{ destination_ip | default("<destination_ip>") }}` / `{{ destination_domain | default("<destination_domain>") }}`:
  ```bash
  iptables -I OUTPUT -d {{ destination_ip | default("<destination_ip>") }} -j DROP
  iptables -I FORWARD -d {{ destination_ip | default("<destination_ip>") }} -j DROP
  # DNS sinkhole the destination domain
  echo "0.0.0.0  {{ destination_domain | default("<destination_domain>") }}" >> /etc/hosts
  ```

{% if exfil_vector | default("https") == "dns" %}
- [ ] **Block DNS exfiltration** – Restrict DNS queries from `{{ source_ip | default("<source_host>") }}` to only the internal resolver:
  ```bash
  iptables -I OUTPUT -s {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }} -p udp --dport 53 \
    ! -d {{ internal_dns | default("10.0.0.1") }} -j DROP
  iptables -I OUTPUT -s {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }} -p tcp --dport 53 \
    ! -d {{ internal_dns | default("10.0.0.1") }} -j DROP
  ```
{% endif %}

{% if exfil_vector | default("https") in ["http", "https"] %}
- [ ] **Block HTTP/HTTPS proxy bypass** – Force all web traffic through the inspecting proxy:
  ```bash
  # Transparent proxy redirect (iptables)
  iptables -t nat -I OUTPUT -s {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }} \
    -p tcp -m multiport --dports 80,443 -j REDIRECT --to-port 3128
  ```
{% endif %}

{% if exfil_vector | default("https") == "usb" or insider_threat | default(false) %}
- [ ] **Physically secure USB / removable media** – Confiscate all USB devices from `{{ source_ip | default("<source_host>") }}`'s physical location. Disable USB ports:
  ```bash
  # Linux – disable USB storage
  echo 'blacklist usb_storage' >> /etc/modprobe.d/blacklist.conf
  rmmod usb_storage 2>/dev/null
  # Windows – disable via registry
  reg add "HKLM\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Services\USBSTOR" /v Start /t REG_DWORD /d 4 /f
  ```
{% endif %}

- [ ] **Start full-packet capture on exfiltration path** – Capture all remaining traffic between `{{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }}` and `{{ destination_ip | default("<destination_ip>") }}`:
  ```bash
  tcpdump -i {{ capture_interface | default("eth0") }} \
    "host {{ source_ip | default("<source_ip>") }} and host {{ destination_ip | default("<destination_ip>") }}" \
    -w /tmp/exfil_{{ source_ip | default("host") }}_$(date +%s).pcap -s 0 &
  echo "PCAP PID: $!"
  ```

- [ ] **Preserve current network connections** – Capture active connections before isolation:
  ```bash
  # Linux
  ss -antp > /tmp/netstat_{{ source_ip | default("host") }}_$(date +%s).txt
  lsof -i > /tmp/lsof_{{ source_ip | default("host") }}_$(date +%s).txt
  # Running processes snapshot
  ps auxf > /tmp/processes_{{ source_ip | default("host") }}_$(date +%s).txt
  ```

- [ ] **Revoke active sessions / credentials** – If cloud or SaaS accounts are involved, revoke all OAuth tokens and API keys immediately:
  ```bash
  {% if cloud_provider is defined and cloud_provider %}
  # {{ cloud_provider }} – revoke IAM credentials
  {% if cloud_provider == "AWS" %}
  aws iam delete-access-key --access-key-id <compromised_key_id> --user-name <user>
  aws iam update-login-profile --user-name <user> --password-reset-required
  {% elif cloud_provider == "GCP" %}
  gcloud iam service-accounts keys delete <key_id> --iam-account=<account>
  {% elif cloud_provider == "Azure" %}
  az ad user revoke-sign-in-sessions --id <user_id>
  az ad app credential delete --id <app_id> --key-id <key_id>
  {% endif %}
  {% else %}
  # Revoke all OAuth tokens for the affected user account
  # Check identity provider (IdP) and revoke active sessions
  {% endif %}
  ```

{% if insider_threat | default(false) %}
- [ ] **⚠️ INSIDER THREAT PROTOCOL** – Do NOT alert the suspected user. Coordinate with HR and Legal before any interview. Preserve all access logs under legal hold.
{% endif %}

{% if c2_suspected | default(false) %}
- [ ] **⚠️ C2 SUSPECTED** – Treat destination `{{ destination_ip | default("<destination_ip>") }}` as C2 infrastructure. Do NOT visit the domain or IP from corporate devices. Submit to threat intel immediately.
{% endif %}

- [ ] **Notify DPO and Legal** – Exfiltration of `{{ data_classification | default("CONFIDENTIAL") }}` data requires immediate notification:
  - DPO: `{{ dpo_contact | default("dpo@phantomnet.local") }}`
  - Legal: `{{ legal_contact | default("legal@phantomnet.local") }}`

