### 🔍 Phase 2 · DLP Review & Policy Hardening `(T+15 → T+90 min)`

> Goal: Understand what DLP missed, fix it, and prevent re-exfiltration.

#### 2a. DLP Alert & Log Review

- [ ] **Pull DLP alert logs for the last `{{ audit_period_hours | default(72) }}` hours**
  - DLP vendor: `{{ dlp_vendor | default("None / Unknown") }}`
  - Policy triggered: `{{ dlp_policy_name | default("N/A") }}`
  - Current mode: `{{ dlp_mode | default("monitor") }}` → **Target: `block`**

  ```bash
  # Symantec DLP – export incidents via REST API
  curl -sk -u admin:$DLP_PASS \
    "https://{{ dlp_host | default("dlp.phantomnet.local") }}/ProtectManager/webservices/v2/incidents" \
    | python3 -m json.tool > /tmp/dlp_incidents_{{ generated_at | default("now") }}.json

  # Microsoft Purview – via PowerShell
  Get-DlpDetailReport -StartDate (Get-Date).AddHours(-{{ audit_period_hours | default(72) }}) `
    -EndDate (Get-Date) | Export-Csv /tmp/purview_dlp_{{ generated_at | default("now") }}.csv
  ```

- [ ] **Identify why DLP did NOT block the exfiltration** – Root-cause analysis:
  - [ ] Was the exfil vector (`{{ exfil_vector | default("https") | upper }}`) covered by a DLP policy?
  - [ ] Was the data encrypted before transfer (DLP bypass via encryption)?
  - [ ] Did the exfil use a non-standard port outside DLP coverage?
  - [ ] Was the data chunked to stay below DLP size thresholds?
  - [ ] Was an allowed application (browser, cloud sync) used as the channel?

{% if encryption_used | default(false) %}
- [ ] **⚠️ Encrypted exfiltration detected** – Standard content inspection cannot scan encrypted payloads. Require SSL/TLS inspection (MITM) on all outbound traffic:
  ```bash
  # Squid proxy – enable SSL bump
  # Add to squid.conf:
  # ssl_bump stare step1 !trusted_sites
  # ssl_bump bump step2 !trusted_sites
  # sslcrtd_program /usr/lib64/squid/security_file_certgen -s /var/lib/squid/ssl_db -M 4MB
  ```
{% endif %}

#### 2b. DLP Policy Gap Analysis

- [ ] **Review coverage for all exfil vectors** – Verify DLP policies exist for:
  - [ ] **HTTP/HTTPS** – outbound web content inspection
  - [ ] **Email (SMTP)** – attachment and body scanning for sensitive content
  - [ ] **Cloud Storage** – block upload to `{{ cloud_provider | default("all") }}` services for unclassified hosts
  - [ ] **DNS** – monitor for DNS tunnelling patterns (high-entropy subdomain queries)
  - [ ] **USB / Removable Media** – endpoint DLP agent policy
  - [ ] **FTP / SFTP** – block or monitor file transfers to non-approved destinations
  - [ ] **Printing** – DLP print policy for SECRET/CONFIDENTIAL documents

- [ ] **Switch DLP to BLOCK mode** – If DLP is in `monitor` mode, switch to `block` immediately:
  ```powershell
  # Microsoft Purview – switch policy to block
  Set-DlpCompliancePolicy -Identity "{{ dlp_policy_name | default("Data Exfiltration Policy") }}" `
    -Mode BlockWithNotify
  ```

- [ ] **Create/update DLP rules for the observed exfil pattern**:
  ```bash
  # Example: block bulk file uploads to external IPs
  # Rule: IF outbound bytes > {{ exfil_bytes | default(10485760) }} in 1 hour THEN block + alert
  # Add rule via DLP vendor management console
  ```

- [ ] **Enable DLP on endpoint agents** – Ensure the DLP agent is installed and active on `{{ source_ip | default("<source_host>") }}` and all hosts in affected segments:
  ```bash
  # Check agent status (Symantec DLP example)
  sc query "Vontu Endpoint Agent"
  # Expected: STATE: 4 RUNNING
  ```

#### 2c. Egress Control Hardening

- [ ] **Audit proxy allow-list** – Remove all non-business destinations from the proxy allow-list for the affected host/VLAN.

- [ ] **Enable egress filtering for sensitive data segments** – Apply strict outbound ACL for any VLAN handling `{{ data_classification | default("CONFIDENTIAL") }}` data:
  ```bash
  # Block direct internet access from internal servers (force proxy)
  iptables -I OUTPUT -s {{ affected_subnet | default("10.0.0.0/8") }} \
    -m multiport --dports 80,443 ! -d {{ proxy_ip | default("10.0.0.1") }} -j DROP
  ```

- [ ] **Review and tighten cloud storage access** – Block access to personal cloud storage (Dropbox, Google Drive, OneDrive personal, WeTransfer) from corporate endpoints:
  ```bash
  # DNS sinkhole personal cloud services
  for domain in dropbox.com drive.google.com onedrive.live.com wetransfer.com; do
    echo "0.0.0.0  $domain" >> /etc/hosts
  done
  ```

- [ ] **Document all findings** – Record DLP gap analysis results in the incident ticket.

